  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1161",
  "title": "Collapsable filters for mobile",
  "body": "Hello,\n\nWe are building a more mobile friendly version of our filters and therefor we want to create collapsable filter boxes. Since we are already using Bootstrap 3 at our site I wanted to use their collapse functionality.\n\nWhen I add the needed html via jQuery to the instantsearch generated html it doesn't work. It seems that it isn't picking up the click event.\n\nWhen I add this:\n\n```\nthis.addEventListener(\"click\", function(){ \n\n            $($(this).data('target')).collapse('toggle');\n        });\n```\n\nThe collapse part works, but it seems that instantsearch is no longer picking up the events.. \n\nYou can see what I mean at https://markputs.nl/algolia.php (make your screen small, javascript can be found in Algolia.js)\n\nThanks.\n",
